{
  "id": "2021-08-30_screen_english",
  "date": "2021-08-30",
  "corner": "screen_english",
  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "What are you saying",
  "movie": "",
  "duration_sec": 794.13,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2021-08-30_screen_english.mp3",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.1,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.1,
      "end": 22.11,
      "text": "GMP Morning Theater 스크린 잉글리쉬 타임"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.11,
      "end": 28.87,
      "text": "8월에 함께하고 있는 영화는 누군가 내 꿈을 만들고 있다면 그들은 과연 누구일까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.61,
      "end": 30.33,
      "text": "Dream Builders"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.33,
      "end": 32.47,
      "text": "딩동댕 맞습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 32.47,
      "end": 40.13,
      "text": "아, 0610님께서 항상 잘 듣고 있지만 문자 보내는 건 오랜만이네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.59,
      "end": 44.51,
      "text": "Dream Builder는 이달 초에 영화를 봐서 더 애정이 가네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 45.07,
      "end": 49.29,
      "text": "월요일이라 조금은 우울하지만 모두들 화이팅입니다. 웃음 웃음"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.29,
      "end": 50.25,
      "text": "화이팅!"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.59,
      "end": 54.55,
      "text": "네, 월요병에 시달리시는 분들이 계신가봐요."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.75,
      "end": 56.71,
      "text": "Yeah, you seem a little down today yourself."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.05,
      "end": 57.41,
      "text": "저요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.59,
      "end": 57.85,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.91,
      "end": 58.41,
      "text": "진짜요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.49,
      "end": 59.11,
      "text": "Your voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.11,
      "end": 64.15,
      "text": "Oh, 목소리가? 그래요. 난 되게 잘 자고 일어났다고 생각했는데."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.29,
      "end": 65.05,
      "text": "아, 오케이, 오케이."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.17,
      "end": 68.35,
      "text": "너무 잤나? 그럴 수도 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.85,
      "end": 74.89,
      "text": "아무튼 요즘에 우리 Dream Builders 덕분에 제가 매 밤마다 꿈을 꾸기를 기대하게 된답니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 75.55,
      "end": 77.83,
      "text": "그래서 뭐 이런 생각도 들더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 77.99,
      "end": 79.91,
      "text": "Dream Interpretation."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.97,
      "end": 80.41,
      "text": "아!"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.65,
      "end": 81.25,
      "text": "꿈 해몽."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.83,
      "end": 82.35,
      "text": "해몽."
    },
    {
      "start": 82.45,
      "end": 82.73,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 82.73,
      "end": 84.03,
      "text": "Dream Interpretation."
    },
    {
      "start": 84.11,
      "end": 86.79,
      "text": "Yeah, it has a long, long history. 그렇지 않나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 86.79,
      "end": 89.11,
      "text": "It started way, way, way back when."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.19,
      "end": 93.51,
      "text": "맞아요. 그러면, do Americans also consider dreams important?"
    },
    {
      "start": 93.91,
      "end": 97.21,
      "text": "I think everyone considers dreams somewhat important."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.31,
      "end": 97.69,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.03,
      "end": 100.19,
      "text": "Because they tell us something about us."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.23,
      "end": 100.73,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.73,
      "end": 101.69,
      "text": "Our subconscious."
    },
    {
      "start": 102.53,
      "end": 107.43,
      "text": "Sometimes we don't even know what we're thinking until we dream it."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.51,
      "end": 107.83,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.83,
      "end": 110.77,
      "text": "And then we connect that dream to our reality."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.77,
      "end": 115.57,
      "text": "There are some dreams that I've kept dreaming since I was young."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.57,
      "end": 119.63,
      "text": "For example, the common one is taking a test."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.79,
      "end": 121.25,
      "text": "You show up to school."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.47,
      "end": 122.65,
      "text": "It's test day."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.93,
      "end": 124.51,
      "text": "You didn't know it was a test day."
    },
    {
      "start": 124.63,
      "end": 125.85,
      "text": "You didn't study."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.37,
      "end": 127.03,
      "text": "It's stressful."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.25,
      "end": 128.13,
      "text": "And I start panicking."
    },
    {
      "start": 128.33,
      "end": 128.57,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.11,
      "end": 130.93,
      "text": "What does that say about me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.93,
      "end": 134.07,
      "text": "저 같은 경우는요, 약간 NG."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.53,
      "end": 134.91,
      "text": "NG?"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.07,
      "end": 135.39,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.65,
      "end": 138.63,
      "text": "무한반복 NG나는 그런 꿈을 꿀 때가 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 138.75,
      "end": 139.35,
      "text": "Oh, you're good."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.63,
      "end": 140.31,
      "text": "GMP NG."
    },
    {
      "start": 141.31,
      "end": 142.09,
      "text": "Take two."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.85,
      "end": 143.51,
      "text": "Ah, really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 143.75,
      "end": 147.25,
      "text": "아무튼 굉장히 식은땀에 흠뻑 젖어가지고 깨일 때가 많이 있더라고요."
    },
    {
      "start": 147.25,
      "end": 155.05,
      "text": "And sometimes I dream about, a long time ago, showing up in a public place with no clothes on, completely nude."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.27,
      "end": 158.37,
      "text": "This is a common dream for many, many people."
    },
    {
      "start": 158.43,
      "end": 158.87,
      "text": "아, 그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 159.23,
      "end": 160.25,
      "text": "You haven't had that one?"
    },
    {
      "start": 160.71,
      "end": 164.55,
      "text": "저는 한 번도 그런 꿈은 꿔본 적이 없어가지고 되게 쇼킹합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 164.87,
      "end": 165.25,
      "text": "아, 예."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.39,
      "end": 166.49,
      "text": "상당히 당황합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 166.63,
      "end": 166.81,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.13,
      "end": 170.75,
      "text": "Anyway, I heard there are quite many dream interpretation books."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.25,
      "end": 172.83,
      "text": "There are so many books."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.89,
      "end": 173.17,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.39,
      "end": 175.17,
      "text": "Such as dream dictionaries."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.45,
      "end": 176.37,
      "text": "이런 것들도 있대요."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.37,
      "end": 176.65,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.71,
      "end": 181.03,
      "text": "There was an American lady who wrote a whole dictionary about dreams."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.39,
      "end": 186.53,
      "text": "And she listed the most common dreams we have and how those are connected to our brains."
    },
    {
      "start": 186.67,
      "end": 187.25,
      "text": "Wow, interesting."
    },
    {
      "start": 187.25,
      "end": 188.97,
      "text": "And how they can tell us about ourselves."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.47,
      "end": 191.65,
      "text": "In the U.S., we also have dream catchers."
    },
    {
      "start": 191.73,
      "end": 191.99,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.35,
      "end": 193.73,
      "text": "They're from 원주민."
    },
    {
      "start": 194.37,
      "end": 195.65,
      "text": "북미 원주민 지대."
    },
    {
      "start": 196.03,
      "end": 197.73,
      "text": "And you hang them on your bed."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.85,
      "end": 201.81,
      "text": "And they're supposed to catch the bad spirits, the bad dreams."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.93,
      "end": 203.93,
      "text": "I saw them several times in the movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.93,
      "end": 209.09,
      "text": "When I was a little kid, I had a dream catcher on my bed to catch my nightmares."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.09,
      "end": 210.09,
      "text": "Oh, 그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.41,
      "end": 217.05,
      "text": "게다가 꿈에서 만약에 픽, 돼지를 보면 소위 이제 Lucky Dream이라고 하잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.19,
      "end": 217.59,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.73,
      "end": 220.21,
      "text": "미국에도 과연 그럴지 되게 궁금했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 220.39,
      "end": 221.43,
      "text": "If you dream about a pig?"
    },
    {
      "start": 221.51,
      "end": 221.65,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 222.01,
      "end": 222.63,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 222.81,
      "end": 222.89,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.31,
      "end": 223.87,
      "text": "Nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 224.25,
      "end": 224.91,
      "text": "I wish."
    },
    {
      "start": 224.91,
      "end": 225.47,
      "text": "그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.61,
      "end": 228.03,
      "text": "이런 문화적인 차이가 있다라는 거 짚어드립니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.03,
      "end": 231.21,
      "text": "아무튼 오늘 장면 먼저 듣고 올게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 231.25,
      "end": 233.72,
      "text": "Can't you see, Helmina?"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.14,
      "end": 236.38,
      "text": "Before we had Jenny, we were happy."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.82,
      "end": 238.92,
      "text": "But now, this whole situation..."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.92,
      "end": 239.54,
      "text": "What are you saying?"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.1,
      "end": 241.26,
      "text": "Hey, listen."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.94,
      "end": 243.34,
      "text": "My mom left me too."
    },
    {
      "start": 244.06,
      "end": 245.58,
      "text": "She chose another life."
    },
    {
      "start": 245.98,
      "end": 249.78,
      "text": "And it's not like your dad and my mom didn't like us."
    },
    {
      "start": 249.78,
      "end": 253.72,
      "text": "I just think they like themselves better."
    },
    {
      "start": 254.28,
      "end": 257.5,
      "text": "If it were up to me, I'd love to be your sister."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.06,
      "end": 259.22,
      "text": "If you'll be mine."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.98,
      "end": 262.6,
      "text": "But that doesn't mean I'll be eating your gross casserole."
    },
    {
      "start": 263.82,
      "end": 266.68,
      "text": "I think they got closer with each other."
    },
    {
      "start": 266.78,
      "end": 267.62,
      "text": "They made up."
    },
    {
      "start": 267.76,
      "end": 268.08,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 268.18,
      "end": 270.04,
      "text": "They went through so much trauma together."
    },
    {
      "start": 270.28,
      "end": 273.22,
      "text": "And now things are looking better."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.46,
      "end": 273.74,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.74,
      "end": 274.8,
      "text": "And they're going to be friends."
    },
    {
      "start": 274.8,
      "end": 280.92,
      "text": "Oh, 제니의 악몽을 통해서 이제 미나도 아픔을 서로 이해하게 된 거잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.44,
      "end": 284.18,
      "text": "자, 주요 표현들 알려주세요."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.7,
      "end": 286.36,
      "text": "This whole situation..."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.36,
      "end": 288.77,
      "text": "이 모든 상황이..."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.77,
      "end": 290.45,
      "text": "If it were up to me..."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.45,
      "end": 292.25,
      "text": "네, 이건 과연 어떻게 해석이 될까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.29,
      "end": 294.09,
      "text": "If it were up to me..."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.09,
      "end": 296.39,
      "text": "It means it's not up to me."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.51,
      "end": 298.85,
      "text": "But if it were my decision..."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.85,
      "end": 301.39,
      "text": "If I could choose what to do..."
    },
    {
      "start": 301.39,
      "end": 302.35,
      "text": "Then..."
    },
    {
      "start": 302.35,
      "end": 303.19,
      "text": "저거, 저거, 저거..."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.19,
      "end": 306.29,
      "text": "네, 아주 명확하게 잘 설명을 해주셨어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 306.81,
      "end": 316.05,
      "text": "내가 결정할 수 있는 일은 아니지만 만약에 내가 결정할 수 있다면, 만약에 나에게 선택권이 있다면 이라는 의미입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.65,
      "end": 317.81,
      "text": "그게 물어보기도 하죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.23,
      "end": 320.73,
      "text": "What would you do if you were me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.85,
      "end": 322.69,
      "text": "Or if you were in my shoes?"
    },
    {
      "start": 322.69,
      "end": 323.05,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 323.51,
      "end": 328.43,
      "text": "이렇게 가정을 통해서 반대되는 상황을 이렇게 이야기를 할 수가 있는 거죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.01,
      "end": 329.57,
      "text": "Gross."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.93,
      "end": 330.61,
      "text": "Gross."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.03,
      "end": 331.67,
      "text": "많이 들어봤죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 331.93,
      "end": 332.09,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.09,
      "end": 332.81,
      "text": "Gross."
    },
    {
      "start": 333.21,
      "end": 333.85,
      "text": "Casserole."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.33,
      "end": 340.95,
      "text": "Gross라는 것은 아무래도 제니가 종종 이야기를 했었던 단어라서 이제는 확실히 이해를 하실 거예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.33,
      "end": 341.69,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.85,
      "end": 342.05,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.23,
      "end": 343.85,
      "text": "역겨운이라는 의미거든요."
    },
    {
      "start": 343.91,
      "end": 345.79,
      "text": "It's part of her regular vocabulary."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.51,
      "end": 347.11,
      "text": "Gross."
    },
    {
      "start": 347.29,
      "end": 349.29,
      "text": "근데 그 뒤에 나오는 게 뭘까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.79,
      "end": 353.03,
      "text": "Casserole is an all-American dish."
    },
    {
      "start": 353.91,
      "end": 357.45,
      "text": "Many, many Americans like to bake a casserole for dinner."
    },
    {
      "start": 357.45,
      "end": 361.83,
      "text": "It's a very common potluck food when we have potluck parties."
    },
    {
      "start": 361.95,
      "end": 362.19,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 362.45,
      "end": 365.35,
      "text": "약간 찜요리 정도라고 생각하면 될까요, 한국에서?"
    },
    {
      "start": 365.55,
      "end": 366.57,
      "text": "Not 찜요리."
    },
    {
      "start": 366.69,
      "end": 368.05,
      "text": "It's like 구운 요리."
    },
    {
      "start": 368.17,
      "end": 368.91,
      "text": "구운 요리."
    },
    {
      "start": 368.91,
      "end": 374.69,
      "text": "You stick a bunch of ingredients in a pot or a pan and you cook it in the oven."
    },
    {
      "start": 375.15,
      "end": 381.47,
      "text": "Basically, you take all your leftovers, 냉장고에 남은 것들 다 털어서 거기 팬에 넣고 굽는 거예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 381.47,
      "end": 382.81,
      "text": "아, 그렇군요."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.99,
      "end": 387.21,
      "text": "아무튼 종종 미나가 이런 casserole이라는 요리를 했었나 봅니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 387.67,
      "end": 392.25,
      "text": "그랬는데 제니가 한 마리 grossed casserole이라고 이야기를 한 장면이었죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 392.27,
      "end": 394.95,
      "text": "Well, casserole 그 맛의 차이가 상당합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 395.51,
      "end": 398.39,
      "text": "They can be very amazing or very ugh."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.41,
      "end": 401.37,
      "text": "어떤 음식이 남았느냐에 따라서 달라질 수 있겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 401.43,
      "end": 401.69,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 401.81,
      "end": 404.75,
      "text": "So, grossed casserole 충분히 공감 가는 표현이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 404.77,
      "end": 405.05,
      "text": "아, 그렇군요."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.17,
      "end": 405.77,
      "text": "네, 감사합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 406.35,
      "end": 407.51,
      "text": "이 내용 한 번 더 들어볼게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 408.92,
      "end": 410.04,
      "text": "Can't you see, 험사?"
    },
    {
      "start": 410.04,
      "end": 412.74,
      "text": "Yeah, before we had Jenny, we were happy."
    },
    {
      "start": 413.08,
      "end": 415.24,
      "text": "But now, this whole situation..."
    },
    {
      "start": 415.24,
      "end": 416.0,
      "text": "What are you saying?"
    },
    {
      "start": 416.48,
      "end": 417.6,
      "text": "Hey, listen."
    },
    {
      "start": 418.2,
      "end": 419.68,
      "text": "My mom left me too."
    },
    {
      "start": 420.4,
      "end": 421.92,
      "text": "She chose another life."
    },
    {
      "start": 422.3,
      "end": 426.12,
      "text": "And it's not like your dad and my mom didn't like us."
    },
    {
      "start": 426.78,
      "end": 430.06,
      "text": "I just think they like themselves better."
    },
    {
      "start": 430.64,
      "end": 433.86,
      "text": "If it were up to me, I'd love to be your sister."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.4,
      "end": 435.56,
      "text": "If you'll be mine."
    },
    {
      "start": 436.02,
      "end": 438.92,
      "text": "But that doesn't mean I'll be eating your gross casserole."
    },
    {
      "start": 438.92,
      "end": 446.16,
      "text": "네, 참 좋으면서 표현은 약간 반대로 하는 경향이 있는 것 같은 제니의 말이었습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 446.26,
      "end": 446.92,
      "text": "마지막에."
    },
    {
      "start": 447.28,
      "end": 450.06,
      "text": "이번에 그 정으로 하는, 정이 많아서 하는 멘트."
    },
    {
      "start": 450.26,
      "end": 451.36,
      "text": "아, 딱 그건 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 451.44,
      "end": 453.28,
      "text": "That doesn't mean I'll be eating your gross casserole."
    },
    {
      "start": 453.42,
